						               													<description>At the height of the Minoan civilization, it is said that there was a game that the nobles used to play, in which they tried to dominate a board by placing borders and pawns, using strategy as well as cunning. The game you are about to play is an approach to this ancient game, one of the first board games ever made!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Overview: &amp;#10;&amp;Delta;&amp;iota;&amp;alpha;&amp;#206;&amp;#175;&amp;rho;&amp;epsilon;&amp;sigma;&amp;iota;&amp;sigmaf; (Division) is a tactical game for two players. During the game, players place borders on the game board, dividing it into areas in which they try to gain the majority by placing pawns.&amp;#10;At the end of the game, each player counts the number of squares in the areas on which they have the majority, and the player with the most squares is the winner.&amp;#10;In case of a tie the game ends in a draw.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Contents:&amp;#10;1 Game Board&amp;#10;18 borders (6 small, 6 medium, 6 large) in two colors&amp;#10;12 pawns (8 small and 4 large) in two colors&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
